channel.title: Help please, It's not a complicated question
channel.description:
Hey I just want to know how to remove objects, There is a room I want to make home but there are objects in there like crates and such, How can i delete them? What file do I look in? Thank you
-Deleter164

item.title: Help please, It's not a complicated question
item.dc:creator: @puffypain puffypain
item.description:
@puffypain wrote:

Go to your client.java in your source folder and search for:

public void Deleteobjects() {

You will probably get a long list of objects, to add a new object to the delete list:

 	       deletethatobject(2789, 4838);

The 2 4-digit numbers are the coordinates of the object, copy that code above and change the coordinates i have to your ones. Type ::mypos using noclip or general knowledge to find the coordinates of the object.

Save, compile and restart the server and log-in to find your OBJECT deleted!
